chunk_content: Describe your rationale for reporting TX_NEW vs. TX_RTT. How are you ensuring that patients that transferred in, experienced an interruption in treatment (IIT), or stopped treatment are NOT being counted in TX_NEW at the time they reinitiate treatment? Data visualization & HTS_TST_POS, TX_NEW, and Linkages by Age and Sex Over Time: use examples: 162 Linkage by Five-Year Age Band: T R E A T M E N T 163 T TX_RTT R E A Description: Number of ART patients who experienced an interruption in treatment (IIT) during any previous T reporting period, who successfully restarted ARVs within the reporting period and remained on M treatment until the end of the reporting period.
